text: The 2020 United States presidential election in North Carolina was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump and running mate Vice President Mike Pence had won 15 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in North Carolina
title: 2020 United States presidential election in North Carolina
